# Additional Polling App Rules

## QR Code & Sharing Patterns
- Use `qrcode.react` library for QR code generation
- Generate unique share URLs using UUIDs
- QR codes should link directly to poll voting page
- Share URLs pattern: `/polls/[id]/vote` or `/share/[shareId]`

## Form Validation Patterns
- Use Zod schemas for form validation
- Validate poll questions (min 10 chars, max 200 chars)
- Validate poll options (2-10 options, each 1-100 chars)
- Show field-level error messages using shadcn/ui

Example Zod schema:
```typescript
const pollSchema = z.object({
  question: z.string().min(10).max(200),
  options: z.array(z.string().min(1).max(100)).min(2).max(10),
  expiresAt: z.date().optional()
})
```

## Real-time Updates
- Use Supabase Realtime for live vote counting
- Update poll results without page refresh
- Show "someone just voted" notifications
- Handle concurrent voting gracefully

## Error Boundaries & Loading States
- Wrap poll components in error boundaries
- Show loading skeletons for poll lists
- Handle network errors gracefully
- Provide retry mechanisms for failed votes

## URL Patterns (Specific Routes)
- `/` - Home page with recent polls
- `/polls` - All polls listing  
- `/polls/create` - Create new poll
- `/polls/[id]` - Poll details and voting
- `/polls/[id]/results` - Results page
- `/polls/[id]/edit` - Edit poll (creator only)
- `/share/[shareId]` - Direct voting via share link